results.description: Disclaimer: I am not an elephant expert. However, I did spend a half day at the Elephant Jungle Sanctuary in Chiang Mai and an afternoon with Wassana (another elephant) in Khao Sok. Frankly, I experienced mixed emotions (wonder, fear, awe, melancholy, discomfort) during both these visits. However, what I liked most about Elephant Jungle Sanctuary was their rescue mission. This is not Wassana. Wassana’s skin was dust grey with light pink patches (scars).  Her eyes were tired. This eye tells a different story. One of curiosity and hope. It is saying, remember: Be gentle, be thoughtful, be kind.
